            <div type="a">
                <column>03</column>
                <head>Cowhiding of Geo. Rye, J. P.</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>George Rye, Justice of the Peace in Woodstock, was cowhided by members of
                    his community after he posted a notice which they believed slandered some
                    "ladies." Rye's notice was intended to stop demonstrations by "rebel
                    sympathizers," including "young women" who were "sometimes strumpeting the
                    streets, singing rebel songs, and making insulting remarks."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
